text: The following lists events that happened in 1950 in Iceland. ==Incumbents== *President - Sveinn Björnsson *Prime Minister - Ólafur Thors, Steingrímur Steinþórsson ==Events== ==Births== Valgerður Sverrisdóttir *13 January - Valgerður Bjarnadóttir, politician. *23 March - Valgerður Sverrisdóttir, politician *16 June - Kristenn Einarsson, publisher *26 August - Steinunn Sigurðardóttir, poet and novelist *3 September - Jóhannes Eðvaldsson, footballer *4 September - Tómas Pálsson, footballer *4 November - Jón Pétursson, footballer ==Deaths== *25 April - Guðjón Samúelsson, architect (b. 1887) ==References== Category:1950s in Iceland Iceland Iceland Category:Years of the 20th century in Iceland
title: 1950 in Iceland
